Based on a quick look at the transit map and what I remember from being in London a long time ago, I don't think the Underground has LOCAL and express trains.

In New York, most subway lines are built with four tracks. The LOCAL trains, which make all the stops, run on the outer tracks.  The express trains, which run on the inner tracks, make only the major stops.  Local stops have platforms on the outer walls of the station, and the express trains on the inner tracks whiz by.  Express stops have platforms between the local and express tracks.

